                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250630-21-victim185 t18250630-21-viclabel104"></join>. The prisoner was my <rs id="t18250630-21-deflabel105" type="occupation">carman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250630-21-defend184 t18250630-21-deflabel105"></join>. On the 9th and 10th of May he took some bricks to Mr. Rowley's; I sent him there for the money a day or two before the 7th of June, on which day he came to book his work, and I asked if he had received the money - he said No, he was to take another thousand bricks the next morning, and they would be paid for altogether.</p>
